  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the types of pain during pregnancy?",
  "response": "During pregnancy, women can experience a variety of types of pain and discomfort, which can vary in intensity and duration. Common types include:\n\n1. **Back Pain**: This is very common due to the extra weight of the baby and changes in posture.\n\n2. **Round Ligament Pain**: Sharp or jabbing pain often felt on one or both sides of the lower abdomen or groin.\n\n3. **Pelvic Pain**: Can be related to the loosening of joints in the pelvic area, often referred to as pelvic girdle pain or symphysis pubis dysfunction.\n\n4. **Headaches**: Often due to hormonal changes, stress, or tension.\n\n5. **Leg Cramps and Restless Leg Syndrome**: Especially common in the third trimester, possibly due to changes in circulation or nutritional deficiencies.\n\n6. **Braxton Hicks Contractions**: Sometimes called \"false labor,\" these are irregular, usually painless contractions.\n\n7. **Sciatica**: Pain that radiates along the sciatic nerve path, from the lower back down to the legs.\n\n8. **Hip Pain**: Often caused by the body preparing for labor, as well as changes in posture.\n\n9. **Rib Pain**: Due to the expanding uterus pushing up against the ribs.\n\n10. **Carpal Tunnel Syndrome**: Tingling or numbness in the hands and fingers caused by swelling compressing the median nerve.\n\n11. **Abdominal Pain**: Often normal, related to expansion and stretching, but should be monitored for signs of something more serious.\n\n12. **Breast Pain and Tenderness**: Caused by hormonal changes and preparation for breastfeeding.\n\nIt's important for pregnant women to discuss any pain or unusual symptoms with their healthcare provider to ensure both their own health and the health of their baby.",
